<h2>Solar Incentives in Chicago</h2>

<p>Chicago residents have access to several substantial solar incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, which will remain at 30% through 2032 before stepping down. Illinois offers additional state-level incentives through the Illinois Shines program, which provides Solar Renewable Energy Credits (SRECs) that can be worth \$1,000-\$3,000 annually depending on system size. ComEd participates in the state's net metering program, allowing customers to receive full retail rate credit for excess solar energy fed back into the grid. Cook County also offers property tax exemptions for solar installations, ensuring that adding solar panels won't increase your property tax burden despite increasing your home's value.</p>

<h2>Best Solar Companies in Chicago</h2>

<p>When selecting a solar installer in Chicago, prioritize companies with extensive experience in cold climate installations and proper Illinois licensing through the Illinois Department of Financial and Professional Regulation. Look for installers who are NABCEP-certified and have specific experience with Chicago's building codes and ComEd interconnection requirements. The best Chicago solar companies offer comprehensive warranties including 25-year panel performance warranties, 10-year inverter warranties, and workmanship guarantees of at least 5-10 years. Verify that potential installers carry proper insurance, have strong local references, and provide detailed production estimates based on Chicago's specific weather patterns and sun exposure data. Companies should also handle all permitting, ComEd interconnection paperwork, and rebate applications on your behalf.</p>

